<br>
Realistically, the only people who have the available resources to make these things on a mass production line scale, are the top end guilds, as they farm the required areas and do not have to BUY the required items in the bazaar. <br>
<br>
Look up prices on Magma Crystals and Metallic Substance, then look up the required amount of each, and then create a trade price and a retail price for these items... No one will buy them because Ornate Molds will be priced lower. <br>
<br>
Untill all the bazaar sluts and top end guilds stop gauging trade skillers, top end smithing items such as PoP armor will continue to not be available.<br>
<br>
Sorry to say... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dexlen>Dexlen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 103<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/8/03 2:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=145.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://lucidchimera.freeservers.com/images/viking.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Elemental Chain</span><hr size=1> I expect component cost + Component Rarity (or p.i.t.a. level) to be the main drawback in obtaining these pieces. I'm also thinking most of the hi end guild trademasters are using the component pieces to outfit their own guildmembers with needed equipment pieces for now. <br>
What I would like to find out is who can and has made these pieces and just a ballpark cost of what they would like to get for them. Also, if there is any farming that can be accomplished (non elemental) to assist or defray some of the costs..<br>
<br>
