<br>
I have a guildee that was able to sell quite a few Drops of Pure Rain for 4k each a month ago.  Why?  Because people would buy them for that much.  Know what price you'll buy for tradeskill stuffs, and stick buy it.  Who CARES if Metallic Substance is listed at 25k?  If there was only one Large Bronze BP in the bazaar, and it was 25k... would you bitch about it?<br>
<br>
IN ADDITION, many of the tradeskill drops in Elemental Planes are extremely rare.  Through the raids that Agony has done I've only gathered enough pieces to try ONE chain combine.  Yay, earth chain booties  =x.<br>
<br>
I expect due to this drop rate, that most guilds will be saving drops for guild use for quite a while.  The EP smithing pieces you see the the bazaar are (I supsect) what people recieve from their own xp groups in EP.  Meanwhile the drops that guilds recieve per raid are used by the guild's tradeskillers.  Certain things (like Magma Crystals and Metalic Substance) may be harder to come by, due to that<br>
